    "comment": "Rationale: Complexin-2 presynaptic immunoreactivity is observed in the Calyx of Held synapse in the brainstem (Fig 11C).\n\nIHC was performed using an antibody (SySy, rabbit anti-Cplx-1/2) that detects Complexin-1 and -2. Complexin-1 KO mice exhibit a loss of immunoreactivity in the somata of the MNTB principal neurons (Fig 11C) indicating the specificity of the antibody for Complexin-1, however immunoreactivity in the presynaptic terminal persist at P7 indicating the presence of Complexin-2.. Experimental description: Cplx1+/+ and Cplx1-/- littermates of either sex were used for most of the experiments...",
